obo:UBERON_0002421  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_2919  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1: \"OPHN1-Homer interaction is critical for LTP\"\n- \"Whereas LTP-inducing stimuli produced a robust and long-lasting potentiation in control neurons, only an initial, transient increase in synaptic transmission was observed in simultaneously recorded neurons coexpressing OPHN1#2 shRNA and OPHN1Hom (Fig. 1A).\"\n\nFig.2: \"OPHN1-Homer interaction is required for positioning EZ near PSD\"\n- \"Consistent with previous findings (Lu et al., 2007), we observed that in scr#1 shRNA-expressing neurons PSD-95-GFP puncta were nearly always associated with clathrin-DsRed (Fig. 2A). In OPHN1#2 shRNA-expressing neurons, however, we noted a considerable loss of PSD-associated clathrin puncta (Fig. 2A).\"\n\nFig.3: \"Disruption of OPHN1-Homer interaction reduces the number of newly exocytosed AMPARs at synaptic sites in basal synaptic conditions\"\n- \"GluA1 exocytosis at synaptic sites was significantly reduced in neurons treated with pep-OPHN1Hom, compared with pep-contHom or no peptide-treated neurons (Fig. 3C,D). \"\n\nFig.4: \"OPHN1-Homer interaction is essential for glycine-induced increase in receptor recycling/exocytosis and synaptic AMPAR number\"\n- \"glycine induced a robust increase in the amount of SEP-GluA1 at the spine surface of these neurons (Fig. 4A-C). In contrast, when neurons were pretreated with pep-OPHN1Hom, only a modest increase in synaptic SEP-GluA1 was observed upon glycine stimulation (Fig. 4A-C)...\". Experimental description: - \"Dissociated hippocampal neurons were prepared from E18 rats\"\n- Species of over-expressed oligophrenin-1 (OPHN1) is human (traced back to PMID:22017989 ): \"The OPHN1-EGFP construct was generated by inserting the human OPHN1 coding sequence into the mammalian expression vector pEGFP-N3 (enhanced GFP, Clontech). \"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-16" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2919" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

